From what's happened in the semester so far, EE 126's workload is roughly the same as CS 170.

----

I think 127 has slightly lower workload than 126.

----

Sounds like three of the heaviest EECS math courses.  If you don't have confidence in your math background, I would recommend taking one; two at most.  EE127 with Prof El Ghaoui was pretty non-trivial, ~25 hr problem sets every two weeks.

Haven't taken 126, but for 127 and 189, strong grasp of linear algebra is key.  I suffered in EE127 quite a bit because my extent of linear algebra maturity was from freshman Math 54.  Having gone through EE127, CS189 is much more manageable this semester.  CS189 with Prof Sahai this semester featured 20+ hr problem sets every ONE week; although the course staff have decided to tone it down to more reasonable ~15 hr psets.
